n, a true character indeed.&#8221;&#8211; Keith Richards: &#8220;One of my big lights has gone out.&#8221;&#8211; Arnold Schwarzenegger: &#8220;When I was 10 years old and I dreamed every night of moving to America, Chuck Berry played the soundtrack. He rocked the world. RIP.&#8221;&#8211; Stephen King: &#8220;Chuck Berry died. This breaks my heart, but 90 years old ain&#8217;t bad for rock and roll. Johnny B. Goode forever.&#8221;-AFP